Meet <b>Sara123</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Sara123's home at <a href='/home/?user=heiress730'>85351 Rosewood Road</a> is the envy of most of her Ravenwood neighbors. She has big sun-filled rooms full of cool toys and furniture, and has plans to add even more space and stuff. Since August 21, 2006, she has impressed fellow citizens with her smarts and style.<br><br>Sara123 definitely makes her voice heard. She's a singer! With a range of three octaves, she can sing many songs that make her music classmates strain. But her interest in music goes beyond performing as a vocalist. She collaborates with other musical friends to create new sounds and textures. So far, she has provided handclaps, whistling and drum beats for her friends' compositions.<br><br>When she isn't making music, Sara123 enjoys listening to music. She puts on disco or world music while curling up with a good book, and listens to punk when she's getting ready for school in the morning. Wherever she goes, she has a soundtrack. <br><br>So, start a conversation with Sara123 about her interests, and you'll see that she's a smart, friendly girl with plenty of creative energy. Maybe some of it will rub off on you! Thanks for being a good citizen, Sara123, and congratulations on being named Citizen of the Week!</div>
